The paper deals with the problem of passive localization of multiple targets using time of arrival (TOA) measurements, which is a common problem in the field of information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The proposed algorithms involve factor graph-based belief propagation, which is a popular technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of particle swarm optimization, which is a common optimization technique in numerical analysis and mathematical optimization (cs.MA). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of improving the position accuracy of receivers, which is a common problem in the field of networked systems and wireless sensor networks (cs.NI).
